Asari Dokubo, a former militant leader, has threatened to kill Nnamdi Kanu, leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB.  Dokubo threatened to kill Kanu inside the courtroom with his bare hands.The former leader of the defunct Movement for the Emancipation of the Niger-Delta issued the threat while reacting to reports that some IPOB members had beaten him up.Dismissing such claims, Dokubo said the day such happens, he will practically go to court and eliminate the IPOB leader personally.In a video shared on his Facebook page, Dokubo described such claims as falsehood.“You can think o, You can talk, but the day you attempt all these your lies that you are lying, I will practically go and kill Nnamdi Kanu even in the court, even with Nigerian Military and all the Nigerian security agencies around.“I will not send anybody, I will practically go there and kill him with my own hands,” he threatened.The Niger Delta warlord and Kanu have experienced a frosty relationship over the years.Kanu is facing charges bordering on terrorism before Justice Binta Nyako-led Federal High Court, Abuja.  Source •Asari Dokubo and Nnamdi Kanu Agitation for an independent state of Biafra suffered a setback Friday with a former Niger Delta militant leader, Asari Dokubo describing the leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) Nnamdi Kanu, as an “idiot.” Asari, a former leader of the Niger Delta People’s Volunteer… In "News" Asking If I’m Biafran Is Like Asking If My Name Is Asari Dokubo – Ex-militant Leader In "News" Former Niger Delta militant Asari Dokubo said a video of him that has gone viral where he was mocking and threatening Nnamdi Kanu's leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra is an old video. According to PM News, reports crediting Dokubo with saying that he would smoke out Kanu and… In "News"